Edited July 28, 2013 by Maxed-Rockets
Moved all designs to this post.

This is Cora. A proven Duna return craft. Should easily do other planets. There's more delta-V than needed for Duna, which is why it's on the large side. It will probably lag a bit upon launch. The craft file attached is all stock. I stripped away the AdamKSP and MechJeb that you can see in the pics. For your own sanity I do recommend those mods though.

It uses lateral style staging. Three stages for ascent to orbit.

Here is the orbiter. This is two lateral style stages, 8 NERVAs each, for total of 16. There is also a droptank, in an unconventional place.

Here we are...

Operational notes

* Detach the first of the lateral booster stage before your gravity turn, since there's no separation motors on it. It's not wasteful though, this stage empties pretty quick.

* The last central booster stage has low thrust-to-weight. Your almost in orbit by then, so it's not a problem. But it's worth being aware of.

* Once you get to orbit, you should disable the central Rockomax 3200 tank that is under the capsule. This will force all engines to draw from the top mounted droptank.

* Do not detach the droptank while doing a burn! Wait until you complete your interplanetary ejection burn first. There's a little separation motor on it to push it away.

* There's plenty of fuel. Go hog wild and have fun.

Edited September 27, 2012 by bsalis

White Lightning: The name of a water slide in a nearby water park. Oh and the name of my stylish and practical mun lander.

Where's the launch tower?

The liftoff stage's TWR is slightly less than optimal, but it gets you cleanly into kerbin orbit at 100km with plenty extra for a TMI.

Initially the decouplers were underpowered, so I added a bit of explosive power to them. click >

< to see it in action.

The lander stage is my result of not wanting to use the typical 2m small engine. I use this design in most of my recent spaceships since I like the looks of it so much.

http://www./?l0vwtm2r5r0ojux

If you have an average computer, you will get lag.

If you have a sub-average computer, the game might crash while attempting to fly this.

I'd like to submit the ManwÃƒÂ« 3 craft for Interplanetary Return Craft consideration.

Supersonic Labs is proud to announce the immediate release of Scarab HLS Mk III LRM, the newest member in our product family of groundbreaking heavy lift interplanetary mission platforms.

Scarab HLS Mk III LRM improves on the maximum payload capacity of its predecessor by over 50% and is capable of transporting nearly 10,000L of liquid rocket fuel (25 standard fuel tanks), along with three brave Kerbalnauts into 100KM orbit. Equipped with two LV-2 Atomic Rocket Engines, a Anatid Robotics AR202 navigation computer, a interplanetary Rendezvous Calculator module, supplementary parachutes and a flexible staging system, Scarab HLS Mk III LRM supports a wide range of manned interplanetary mission profiles.

Two variants are provided, one being 0.17 stock (ST) and the other requiring MechJeb and Protracter - Rendezvous Calculator mods.

Download - Scarab HLS Mk III LRM (KSP 0.17 stock), MechJeb optional, Protracter - Rendezvous Calculator optional

@Maxed-Rockets, thanks for adding Scarab HLS, but it believe it belongs under Interplanetary Return category, the release spec was tested to go to Duna, land, and return to Kerbin.

It hasn't been tested on other interplanetary bodies yet, but being Duna-return capable should give it enough delta-v to to land and return from some of the moons around the system as well.

The only planet I know it can't return from is Eve, but I haven't heard of a stock ship that can yet..
